</iframe> </template>
</a>
</p>
<figcaption>Here's the Battlefield 6 multiplayer trailer!<a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=wFGEMfyAQtI" rel="noopener" target="_blank">Watch on YouTube</a></figcaption></figure>


<p>What this means for Battlefield 6 players who buy a physical version is you'll simply be able to slap in your physical copy and get straight to playing, which is a bit of a rarity these days.</p>
<p>Other info was revealed about the game courtesy of Grecea's early copy, including the online servers being up-and-running already. Apparently there are even a few people already online and playing, which is fun.</p>
<p>EA and Battlefield Studios <a href="https://www.eurogamer.net/free-battlefield-6-seasonal-content-plans-unveiled-first-batch-arrives-a-few-weeks-after-launch">recently revealed the post-launch content plan for Battlefield 6</a>, which will start coming to the game on the 28th October. New modes, new maps, weapons and more will be added to the game entirely for free.</p>



